For example, LocARNA creates a multiple alignment based on sequence and structure simultaneously. Based on this tool larger genomic regions up to 800 nt can be reliable predicted as shown for coronaviruses (Fig. 3
) (Madhugiri et al., 2014) and HCV (Fig. 4
) (Fricke et al., 2015). Nowadays, long-range interactions (LRIs) are computationally predictable by tools such as LRIscan (Fricke and Marz, 2016), suggesting circularizations of viruses during replication.
